parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump control module can cause the fuel pump to run continuously, resulting in a drained battery and/or a no-start condition, or cause a loss of motive power while the vehicle is in motion, which can increase the risk of a crash causing injury and/or damage to property.
symptoms: the vehicle is unable to start
the vehicle experiences a loss of motive power while in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag control module can cause the airbag warning lamp to illuminate, indicating a potential safety risk, and may prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of a crash.
symptoms: steering wheel buttons/controls do not work
error message "ERROR: DRIVER AIRBAG" appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag warning lamp to illuminate, indicating a potential safety risk, and may prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of a crash.
symptoms: steering wheel buttons/controls do not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An interruption in electrical power to the fuel pump control module can cause the fuel pump to run continuously, resulting in a drained battery and/or a no-start condition, or cause a loss of motive power while the vehicle is in motion, which can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: loss of motive power while the vehicle is in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause the system to disengage unexpectedly, which can lead to a loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: warning lamps are illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering wheel clock spring can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to a failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash, which can increase the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: the horn and buttons on the steering wheel stop working
noise from the steering wheel while turning.
